import React, { useState } from 'react' import TopNav from '../components/TopNav' import { Container, Row, Col, Card, Form, Button } from 'react-bootstrap' import { predictSingle } from '../services/api' import { toast } from 'react-toastify' export default function PredictSingle() { // FULL STUDENT PAYLOAD (same fields your ML API expects) const [form, setForm] = useState({ passed_out_10: 2022, passed_out_11: 2023, passed_out_12: 2024, marks_10: 80, marks_11: 80, marks_12: 80, family_income: 20000, family_members: 4, academic_score: 75, motivation_level: 3, attendance_rate: 80, district: "Chennai", school_type_10: "Government", school_type_11: "Government", school_type_12: "Government", orphan: "No", single_parent: "No", girl_child: "No", communication_frequency: "Medium", family_support: "Medium", extra_curricular: "No", interest_level: "Medium", attitude: "Respectful", school_fee_6_to_12: "10k-20k" }); const [result, setResult] = useState(null); const updateField = (key, val) => { setForm(prev => ({ ...prev, [key]: val })); } const submit = async (e) => { e.preventDefault(); try { const res = await predictSingle(form); // sends FULL JSON setResult(res); toast.success("Prediction successful"); } catch (err) { toast.error("Prediction failed"); } } return ( <>
Single Student Prediction
Academic Score updateField("academic_score", +e.target.value)} /> Motivation Level (1–5) updateField("motivation_level", +e.target.value)} /> Attendance Rate (%) updateField("attendance_rate", +e.target.value)} />
Prediction Result
{result ? ( <>

Dropout Probability: {result.dropout_probability}

Deservingness Score: {result.deservingness_score}

Risk Tier: {result.risk_tier}

) : (

No result yet — fill fields and predict.

)} ) }
